General.Name: Infant Bacterial Therapeutics AB (publ)
General.Description: Infant Bacterial Therapeutics AB (publ), a clinical stage pharmaceutical company, develops drugs to prevent or treat rare diseases affecting premature infants in Sweden. The company's lead drug candidate is IBP-9414, to prevent necrotizing enterocolitis, as well as to improve feeding tolerance affecting premature infants. It is also developing IBP-1016 for the treatment of gastroschisis, a rare and severe disease in infants. The company was incorporated in 2011 and is based in Stockholm, Sweden.
